fect).\n\nC:\\Users\\Usuario\\Documents\\DOC JOSE\\DEV\\goldpainting\\src\\app\\components\\GoogleReviewsCarousel.tsx:206:7\n  204 |   useEffect(() => {\n  205 |     if (page > pages.length) {\n> 206 |       setPage(1);\n      |       ^^^^^^^ Avoid calling setState() directly within an effect\n  207 |     }\n  208 |   }, [page, pages.length]);\n  209 |","@next/next/no-img-element","Using `<img>` could result in slower LCP and higher bandwidth. Consider using `<Image />` from `next/image` or a custom image loader to automatically optimize images. This may incur additional usage or cost from your provider. See: https://nextjs.org/docs/messages/no-img-element","JSXOpeningElement",["391"],{"kind":"392","justification":"393"},"directive",""]